    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.101/4</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 204</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-15">February 15,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that since mailing my
                    despatch No. 203 of February 14, 1935, the Legation has learned that the French
                    Government has likewise informed the Egyptian Government that it reserves all
                    rights regarding the changes effected in the administration of Alexandria by the
                    “unilateral procedure” of the Decree-Law of January 1, 1935, and the Ministerial
                    Orders of January 2, 1935.</p>
                <p>The Legation also hears that some of the foreign residents of Alexandria may
                    decide to test the validity of the new municipal administration by causing
                    themselves to be sued in the Mixed Courts for refusal to pay taxes.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bert Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
